cant we also set the environment variable in the config?
Yes, absolutely! That's a much better approach. You can add it to your cypress.config.ts:

```typescript
import { defineConfig } from 'cypress';

export default defineConfig({
  env: {
    NEXT_PUBLIC_BREEZE_URL: 'http://local-solar.otovo.com:3000',
    NEXT_PUBLIC_SHORT_INACTIVITY_DETECTION: true,  // Added this line
  },

  retries: {
    runMode: 2,
  },

  blockHosts: ['*googletagmanager.com', '*hsforms*'],
  e2e: {
    setupNodeEvents() {
      // implement node event listeners here
    },
  },
  defaultCommandTimeout: 20000,
  video: true,
});
```

Then we can simplify the test by removing the environment variable setting from the beforeEach:

```javascript
import calcCreated from '../fixtures/interestApi/interestCalcCreated.json';

describe('Calculation page physical version', () => {
  beforeEach(() => {
    // Stub timer-related functions
    cy.clock();

    // Set physical store data in localStorage before visit
    cy.window().then((win) => {
      win.localStorage.setItem(
        'utm_data',
        JSON.stringify({
          utm_medium: 'physical',
          utm_source: 'partner',
          utm_campaign: 'test-store',
          utm_content: 'test-store',
          utm_id: '',
        })
      );
    });

    // Setup API intercepts
    cy.intercept('GET', `**/web/interests/${calcCreated.id}/`, calcCreated)
      .as('interestDetail');
    cy.intercept(
      'GET',
      `**/web/interests/${calcCreated.id}/products/`,
      calcCreated.products
    ).as('products');
    cy.intercept('GET', '**/web/customforms/**', {}).as('customForms');
    cy.intercept('POST', '**/web/campaigns/generate-referral-code/', {
      url: 'https://foo.bar',
    }).as('referralCode');
  });

  // Rest of the test remains the same...
});
```

This is much cleaner as:
1. The environment variable is set once in the config
2. It's available for all tests
3. It's more maintainable
4. It follows the principle of configuration over code

