what's the recommended way of "ending" a test?
In Cypress, there are several recommended ways to "end" a test, depending on what you're verifying. Here are the common patterns:

```javascript
describe('Test ending patterns', () => {
  it('1. Verify final URL', () => {
    cy.visit('/some-page');
    // ... test actions ...

    // End by verifying the final URL
    cy.url().should('include', '/expected-final-page');
  });

  it('2. Verify final state', () => {
    // End by checking the final state of the UI
    cy.get('[data-testid="success-message"]')
      .should('be.visible')
      .and('contain', 'Operation completed');
  });

  it('3. Verify network request completion', () => {
    cy.intercept('POST', '/api/submit').as('submitRequest');
    // ... test actions ...

    // End by verifying the request was successful
    cy.wait('@submitRequest')
      .its('response.statusCode')
      .should('eq', 200);
  });

  it('4. Multiple final conditions', () => {
    // End by checking multiple conditions together
    cy.get('[data-testid="final-state"]').should(($el) => {
      expect($el).to.be.visible;
      expect($el.text()).to.include('Success');
      expect($el.hasClass('completed')).to.be.true;
    });
  });

  it('5. Verify and cleanup', () => {
    // End with verification and cleanup
    cy.get('[data-testid="success-state"]').should('be.visible')
      .then(() => {
        // Clean up any test data
        cy.task('cleanupTestData');
      });
  });
});
```

For your specific inactivity test, I would recommend something like:

```javascript
it('should redirect after extended inactivity', () => {
  cy.visit(`http://localhost:3000/es-es/solar/redirect/${calcCreated.id}`);

  // Wait for initial page load
  cy.url().should('include', 'products');

  // Advance time past the redirect threshold
  cy.tick(2000); // Assuming 2 seconds is past your redirect threshold

  // End by verifying the redirect
  cy.url().should('include', '/physical-store')
    .and('include', 'utm_medium=physical')
    .then(() => {
      // Optional: Log final state for debugging
      cy.log('Test completed: Verified redirect to physical store');
    });
});

it('should show warning and allow user to stay', () => {
  cy.visit(`http://localhost:3000/es-es/solar/redirect/${calcCreated.id}`);

  // Show warning
  cy.tick(1000);

  // Verify warning and interact
  cy.get('[data-testid="inactivity-monitor"]')
    .should('be.visible')
    .within(() => {
      cy.get('button').click();
    });

  // End by verifying user remains on original page
  cy.url().should('include', 'products')
    .and('not.include', 'physical-store');

  // And warning is dismissed
  cy.get('[data-testid="inactivity-monitor"]')
    .should('not.exist');
});
```

Key principles for ending tests:
1. Always end with a positive assertion of the expected final state
2. Verify the most important/relevant final condition
3. Make sure all async operations are complete
4. Clean up if necessary
5. Keep it focused on what matters for the test case
6. Make it clear what constitutes success

